WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.120
What I observed a lot of my career is how players study film because now it's become like you

00:00:11.120 --> 00:00:16.080
watch game film you see what you do right you see what you do wrong okay let's do more of

00:00:16.080 --> 00:00:21.800
that let's do less of that right but the way I grew up from Tex winter Phil Jackson the

00:00:21.800 --> 00:00:26.039
way film was broken down it was broken down to the smallest detail it was broken down

00:00:26.039 --> 00:00:32.240
to the right angle is broken down to foot placement timing looking at the posture

00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:36.600
of a teammate you know what can he be thinking what can he be feeling same

00:00:36.600 --> 00:00:40.600
thing with the opposition you know you watch the feed watch players going to the

00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:44.399
timeouts who's talking to who who's not talking you start looking at every

00:00:44.399 --> 00:00:50.000
little thing and so watching the game for me would take like five hours and that

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.399
attention to details what's missing so I felt like if I can put that in a show

00:00:53.399 --> 00:00:58.119
I have the next generation these eleven-year-old kids 12-year-old kids start

00:00:58.119 --> 00:01:02.399
watching the game at that level what are they going to be when they're 25 you

00:01:02.399 --> 00:01:07.359
know what level would they be at then and it's a passion of mine to get that

00:01:07.359 --> 00:01:11.840
thing going like I said April 12th would be the first episode

